==International relations==

===Twin towns&nbsp;— Sister cities===
Buffalo has a number of [[Twin towns and sister cities|sister cities]] as designated by [[Sister Cities International]] (SCI):<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sister-cities.org/interactive-map/Buffalo,%20New%20York|title=Interactive City Directory|publisher=Sister-cities.org}}, Retrieved 2013-5-31.</ref><ref>[http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/OurCity/Buffalo_Sister_Cities Sister Cities] from Buffalo's website</ref>
*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Lille]], France (1989)<ref>{{cite web | title =Lille, France&nbsp;— City of Buffalo | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/OurCity/Buffalo_Sister_Cities/Lille_France | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Dortmund]], Germany (1972)<ref>{{cite web | title =Dortmund, Germany&nbsp;— City of Buffalo | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/OurCity/Buffalo_Sister_Cities/Dortmund_Germany | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Siena]], Italy (1961)<ref>{{cite web | title =Siena, Italy&nbsp;— City of Buffalo | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/OurCity/Buffalo_Sister_Cities/Siena_Italy | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Torremaggiore]], Italy<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.buffalonews.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20130316/LIFE/130319351/1057|date=March 16, 2013|author=Kearns, Michelle|title=Sister cities, a banquet of international friendships|publisher=[[The Buffalo News]]}}, Retrieved 2013-5-31.</ref>
*{{flagicon|JAM}} [[Saint Ann Parish, Jamaica|Saint Ann]], Jamaica (2007)<ref>{{cite news | title =Buffalo gains sister city: St. Ann, Jamaica | work =Buffalo News | url =http://www.buffalonews.com/cityregion/buffaloerie/story/166115.html?imw=Y | date =September 19, 2007 | accessdate =2008-12-24|archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070925055948/http%3A//www.buffalonews.com/cityregion/buffaloerie/story/166115.html%3Fimw%3DY |archivedate = September 25, 2007|deadurl=yes}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Kanazawa, Ishikawa|Kanazawa]], [[Ishikawa Prefecture]], Japan (1962)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japaninbuffalo.org/bksc.html|title=Buffalo-Kanazawa Sister City Committee|publisher=Japan in Buffalo.org.}}, Retrieved 2013-5-31.</ref>
*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Rzeszów]], Poland (1974)<ref name="Rzeszów">{{cite web |url=http://www.rzeszow.pl/miasto-rzeszow/wspolpraca-miedzynarodowa/miasta-partnerskie-rzeszowa|title=Serwis informacyjny UM Rzeszów&nbsp;— Informacja o współpracy Rzeszowa z miastami partnerskimi |publisher=www.rzeszow.pl |accessdate=2013-05-31}}</ref><ref name="Rzeszów-Buffalo">{{cite web | title =History | publisher =Buffalo-Rzeszow Sister Cities, Inc. | url =http://www.brsc.us/history/index.htm | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Tver]], Russia (1989)<ref>{{cite web | title =Tver, Russia&nbsp;— City of Buffalo | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/OurCity/Buffalo_Sister_Cities/Tver_Russia | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Yeongcheon]], [[North Gyeongsang Province]], South Korea (2011)<ref>{{cite web | title =Buffalo has new sister city in South Korea: November 2&nbsp;- WIVB Channel 4 | publisher =WIVB | url=http://www.wivb.com/dpp/news/buffalo/Buffalo-has-new-sister-city-in-S-Korea | accessdate =2011-11-02}}</ref>

===Partnerships===
Buffalo also has partnerships with the following towns:<ref>{{cite web | title =Buffalo Sister-Cities | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/files/1_2_1/city_departments/SPlanning/pdfs/SisterCitiesBrochure.pdf | accessdate =2009-12-29}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|GHA}} [[Cape Coast]], Ghana
*{{flagicon|NIR|union}} [[Derry]], [[Northern Ireland]], UK
*{{flagicon|UKR}} [[Drohobych]], Ukraine (2001)<ref>{{cite web | title =Buffalo and Drohobych join ranks of sister cities| work = The Ukrainian Weekly | date =April 1, 2001 | url =http://www.ukrweekly.com/Archive/2001/130120.shtml | accessdate =2008-12-24|archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070930033451/http%3A//www.ukrweekly.com/Archive/2001/130120.shtml |archivedate = September 30, 2007|deadurl=yes}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|UKR}} [[Horlivka]], Ukraine (2007)<ref>{{cite web | title =Buffalo, N.Y. and Horlivka, Ukraine Foster Sister City Relationship | publisher =City of Buffalo, New York | url =http://www.ci.buffalo.ny.us/Home/Mayor/Archive_Press_Releases/Leadership/2007Archives/May_2007/BUFFALONYANDHORLIVKAUKRAINEFOSTERSISTER | date =May 25, 2007 | accessdate =2008-12-24}}</ref>
*{{flagicon|South Sudan}} [[Juba]], [[South Sudan]]
*{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Kiryat Gat]], Israel
*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Marília]], Brazil

While there is no formal relationship, Buffalo and [[Toronto]] enjoy a close link and friendly rivalry.

